Events.Text: Say hello to the AI assistant and ask for help (see instructions on the left). [instruction 1 of 6]
Hello.
Try to get an appointment as soon as possible (right now it is 10 pm on Thursday). [instruction 2 of 6]
Hello
Hello, how can I help?
I need to make an appointment with Dr. Johnson ASAP.
Keep asking for other times until the assistant has found a slot for you. Engage in smalltalk once this is done. [instruction 3 of 6]
symptoms
Could you describe your symptoms, please?
Cough and a sore throat for two days now. I'm miserable.
Say something about Dr. Johnson, the AI Assistant, or something that has happened to you today. Be creative! [instruction 4 of 6]
patient name
Could I have your name, please?
John.
It occurs to you that you also want to make an appointment to get your kid Ben vaccinated. Perhaps you can schedule a second appointment at the same time? [instruction 5 of 6]
10 am appointment
Looks like we can do a 10 am appointment this Thursday.
That's a week from now so that's too long. Is there not anything sooner?
Friday at 8 am
What day of the week would you like to schedule the appointment for?
Friday, tomorrow, at the latest if possible.
Keep going until both yours and your kid's appointments are made (this should take a few more turns). Then say goodbye. [instruction 6 of 6]
Okay Friday at 8 am it is.
Okay Friday at 8 am works for us, see you there!
Oh, I just had a huge brain fart! I need to get my son Ben's shots too. Can I schedule him around the same time?
Sure
I am sorry, I don't quite understand what you mean. I am only able to help you book an appointment with your doctor.
He needs his shots so he can go to school, you know what I mean? He's a baby about it, but it's good for him. I told him that today.
s
Sure thing, it will be taken care of.
So my son can be scheduled at the same time as my appointment?
Sure
Sure, thank you.

Scenario.UserTask: You are John and would like to make an appointment with Dr. Johnson for today (Thursday). You have had a cough and a sore throat,  for two days now.
Scenario.WizardTask:
Follow the flow charts and help the user. Some facts you should be aware of: 

* Right now it is Thursday, 10 pm

UserQuestionnaire.Question: Did the assistant stay calm and helpful throughout the dialogue?

WizardQuestionnaire.Question: Did the user change his/her mind about what he/she wants at any time?
Did the user become aggressive or annoyed during the dialogue? (Note: some users may be instructed to be annoying.)
Where you unsure about what to do at any time? (Feel free to send us an email with details.)
